                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                       The scribe,
                        Walda Mikāʾel, is mentioned in the supplication formulas on <locus target="#4rb">4rb</locus>, 11va, 27vb-28ra.
                        <date>Late 19th - early 20th
                           century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; incipits and headings of the texts;
                           names of the scribe and donor; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">-The Vita (fols. 4ra-33ra) is divided into monthly
                              readings from Maskaram (<locus target="#4r">fol. 4r</locus>) up to
                              Mäggäbit (<locus target="#15v">fol. 15v</locus>), with the names of
                              the months written in the upper margin of the fols.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>Supplication written in a different, recent hand, <locus target="#68vb">fol.  68vb</locus>: ወይበልሕ፡ እምስፍ፡ በትንብልና፡ ለእግዝእትነ፡ ማርያም፡ ወላዲተ፡ አምላክ፡ ወበስዕለቶሙ፡ ለኵሎሙ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወሰማዕት…</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>Conjuration written by a recent hand, <locus target="#70v">fol.  70v</locus>: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ በአፈ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፨ ይርኅቅ፡ ሰይጣን።</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>Crude drawings in pencil (fols. 1r; 2r; 3r) </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>Pen trials in pencil and ink (fols. 1rv; 2v; 3rv) -The title of the text is crudely written (in yellow) on the front cover: ቀ. ጀወርግስ</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
